# REQUIRED FOR EVERY INTERACTION:

1. Read .cursor/icr.mdx at the start of each interaction
2. **Testing:** When you add or change behavior (new code, bug fixes, refactors), you MUST:
   - Add or update specs that cover the behavior (or the fix). Do not leave new/changed code untested.
   - Run the relevant specs (and any obviously related specs) before finishing. Fix any failures.
   - Prefer adding a focused spec file for new services/features; run the full spec suite for the touched area.
3. When working on payroll or timesheet workflow features (e.g. payroll index, pay periods, timesheet approval), read and follow the plan at .cursor/plans/payroll_workflow_redesign_80191109.plan.md and document progress in .cursor/icr.mdx (Feature Documentation or Phase 6/7 checklist).
4. Before ending ANY response, if you've learned anything useful about project-specific architectural details that are NOT immediately obvious from reading the code, you MUST update .cursor/icr.mdx with this information
5. When updating .cursor/icr.mdx:
   - Document only (a) non-obvious quirks or gotchas, or (b) overarching design/architectural decisions. Do not document implementation details that are obvious from reading the code or that will change as features iterate (no variable names, field names, or step-by-step flow).
   - Only add new information not already documented
   - Place information in the appropriate section; if no appropriate section exists, create one
